definitions.definition: The office or role of president .
examples: After many years as a party leader, she finally ascended to the presidency .

definitions.definition: The bureaucratic organization and governmental initiatives devolving directly from the president.
examples: Because of the president's lame duck status, the presidency was often hampered by congressional actions.

definitions.definition: The time during which one is president; a president's term of office.
examples: In France, a presidency lasts for five years.
Ernest was a historian specializing in the presidency of Herbert Hoover.

definitions.definition: A supreme local council made up of three persons; ( usually capitalized; also First Presidency ) the highest authority.
One of the three original provinces of British India .
The role of ordained clergy in the celebration of the Eucharist in some denominations.
